The world is encoded with the data of our predecessors. We weren't aware of it, but the connection to nature we experienced was the touching of our great ancestors. 

Earth is a server, housing the data of the ones who came before us, but over time, we lost the ability to read it's information. As we grew more powerful, we stopped looking outward. The world became a canvas for our personal pursuits and the data was slowly wiped away. 

The more walls we built, the larger the gap between our ancestral selves widened. 

